---
import ComingSoonRoomLayout from '../layouts/ComingSoonRoomLayout.astro';
---
<ComingSoonRoomLayout
  room="stacks"
  title="The Stacks"
  subtitle="References, citations, bibliography."
  sourceId="coming-soon-stacks"
>
  <p>
    The Stacks will hold the master bibliography for everything published
    anywhere in the Library — books, scholarly articles, court opinions,
    state reports, federal documents, newspaper coverage. Every claim made
    in any room cites a source; the source lives here, with a brief
    description and where to find it.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Why this room matters.</strong> A library that doesn't show its
    work isn't a library; it's an opinion. The Stacks is the room that
    makes the rest of the Library citable. A reader who wants to verify a
    number, a date, or a quotation will find the path from here.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>What's on every shelf.</strong> Each topical shelf will carry a
    curated reading list for that topic — a "where to start" path for the
    citizen new to the subject, plus deeper rows for the scholar. Margaret
    Bird's <em>Schools of the Republic</em> sits at the front of the
    institutional-history shelf; Cardozo's <em>Meinhard</em> is at the
    front of the fiduciary-doctrine shelf.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Lost Books.</strong> A shelf at the back of the room is reserved
    for the books that should have been written, weren't, and now can't be.
    School-trust history is full of those.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Being planned.</strong> The first topical reading list goes up
    at the end of the summer.
  </p>
</ComingSoonRoomLayout>
